
[1]fan

   FAN, n. [L. vannus.]

   1. An instrument used by ladies to agitate the air and cool the face in
   warm weather. It is made of feathers, or of thin skin, paper or taffety
   mounted on sticks, &c.

   2. Something in the form of a woman's fan when spread, as a peacoc's
   tail, a window, &c.

   3. An instrument for winnowing grain, by moving which the grain is
   thrown up and agitated, and the chaff is separated and blown away.

   4. something by which the air is moved; a wing.

   5. An instrument to raise the fire or flame; as a fan to inflame love.
